{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Review processes for DV and sexual assault victim to appeal not guilty verdict",
        "additional_details": "Current laws makes it very challenging for survivors to appeal. We need a specialised review process to ensure justice\r\n\r\nIn our view, the criminal justice system is deeply imbalanced. Defendants can appeal guilty verdicts, yet it is very difficult for victims of sexual abuse and domestic violence to challenge 'not guilty' verdicts\u2014even with new evidence or procedural failures. We need a specialised review of the threshold to allow victims of these crimes to appeal.",
        "background": "We call on Government to review and make it easier for victims of sexual abuse and domestic violence to appeal 'not guilty' verdicts when significant new evidence emerges or procedural failures occurred. ",
